tip.text: Garlic pork is the bomb
Impromptu visit - best decision made! Love the song selection and food (especially the chef's pizza) was so good!
First time here. Tried the muffins (super moist and yum) and the pan mee soup, very flavourful. Only thing is that it is a bit stuffy and hot in the afternoon.
Had the lunch set last week and the green curry was just so good! Squid as appetizer wasn't great, just very light batter - squid wasn't marinated much so a bit bland. Pandan drink was yummy!
Bit pricey for the amount of meat I got despite ordering a large. My mum said it's not normal - well it's always a first time! And it had to be my plate. Not sure if I'll be back.
